Preheat a well-oiled #grill{} to medium heat.

> TIP: If using a grill pan, you'll heat it in step 4.

Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Using the tip of a #spoon{}, remove and discard black gills from undersides of @Portobello Mushrooms{2}; trim any large stems if necessary. Halve mushrooms. Halve, core, and quarter @Bell Pepper{1}. Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%oz} lengthwise. Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}. Pick @Parsley{¼%oz} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

In a large #bowl{}, toss mushrooms and bell pepper with @Olive Oil{3%tbsp} (@Olive Oil{6%tbsp} for 4 servings), @Italian Seasoning{2%tsp} (@Italian Seasoning{4%tsp} for 4; you'll use the rest later), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}.

Place tomatoes and garlic in the center of a small piece of #foil{}. Drizzle with half the @Balsamic Vinegar{5%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Season with a pinch of @Sugar{pinch}, salt, and pepper. Cinch into a packet.

Pat @Salmon{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; lightly oil with @Cooking Oil{2%tsp}. Season with remaining Italian Seasoning and a pinch of salt and pepper. Place on a large piece of foil, skin sides down.

> TIP: If using a grill pan, skip foil under salmon.

> PAN ALTERNATIVE: Skip foil packet. (You'll cook tomatoes and garlic in step 4.)

Once water is boiling, add @Penne Pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Drain and return pasta to pot. Immediately stir in @Pesto{4%tbsp}, @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1}, and remaining vinegar.

> TIP: Cover pot with lid to keep warm.

> PAN ALTERNATIVE: Stir in half the vinegar (you'll use the rest in the next step).

Add mushrooms, bell pepper, tomato and garlic packet, and salmon to grill. (TIP: For a grill pan, lightly oil; heat over medium high. Cook in batches.) Grill mushrooms, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Grill bell pepper, packet, and salmon until cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} per side.

> PAN ALTERNATIVE: Cook bell pepper in a large oiled pan over medium-high heat, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add mushrooms; cook ~{3-5%minutes} more. Remove; wipe out pan. Cook tomatoes and garlic in olive oil, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining vinegar, @Butter{1%tbsp} (@Butter{2%tbsp} for 4), a pinch of sugar, salt, and pepper. Remove; wipe out pan. Cook salmon, skin sides down, in oil, ~{5-7%minutes}; flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Reserve @Parsley{1%tbsp} (@Parsley{2%tbsp} for 4 servings); set aside.

Thinly slice mushrooms and bell pepper crosswise; add to pot with penne. Stir in half the @Parmesan Cheese{¼%cup} and remaining parsley. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Transfer tomato mixture from foil packet to a small bowl. Cut @Butter{1%tbsp} (@Butter{2%tbsp} for 4 servings) into four pieces; add to bowl along with reserved parsley. Stir until butter has melted.

Place pasta salad in a #serving bowl{} and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Place salmon on a #serving plate{} and top with balsamic tomatoes. Serve family style (or divide between plates and serve).

> PAN ALTERNATIVE: Place tomato mixture in a small bowl and stir in reserved parsley.